        <div id="olive-oil" class="tab-content hidden">
            <section class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">ü´í Olive Oil: A Deep Dive into Syria's Liquid Gold</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">Olive oil is not just a commodity in Syria; it's a cornerstone of its agricultural heritage and culinary identity. With a significant global production share and unique local cultivars, Syria has the potential to elevate its olive oil sector by focusing on premium quality, eco-friendly processing, and complete valorization of by-products. This deep dive explores the opportunity for a world-class olive oil industry in Syria.</p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">The Syrian Olive Oil Landscape</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-green-200">
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Production & Cultivars:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-green-800 space-y-1">
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üìà</span>Projected output: 105,000 MT for 2024/2025 season.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üåç</span>Accounts for ~3% of global olive oil production.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üå≥</span>Unique local cultivars: 'Sorani' (high oil), 'Zaity', 'Doebli', 'Qaisi' (dual-purpose), 'Abbadi Abu-Ghabra' (table olive).</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</span>Challenges: Quality consistency, oxidation, meeting IOC standards.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-200">
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-2">Market Potential & Trends:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-amber-800 space-y-1">
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üåü</span>Strong global demand for premium/organic Extra Virgin Olive Oil (EVOO).</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">‚úàÔ∏è</span>Key export markets: EU, North America, Gulf countries.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üåø</span>Growing market for natural bioactive compounds from olive pomace.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üîç</span>Consumer interest in traceability, origin-specific products, and sustainable practices.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Eco-Friendly Processing & Total Valorization</h3>
                <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">A modern Syrian olive oil facility should prioritize sustainability from grove to bottle. This means water-efficient two-phase decanters, renewable energy (solar), organic certification support, and innovative use of by-products.</p>
                <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
                    <div class="sustainability-illustration"><span class="sustainability-illustration-icon">üíß</span><span><strong>Water Efficiency:</strong> Implementing two-phase decanters to drastically reduce water usage compared to traditional methods. Focus on OMWW treatment for reuse or safe disposal.</span></div>
                    <div class="sustainability-illustration"><span class="sustainability-illustration-icon">‚ôªÔ∏è</span><span><strong>By-Product Valorization:</strong> Transforming olive pomace into bioactives, animal feed, bioenergy (biogas/pellets), and compost, achieving near-zero waste.</span></div>
                    <div class="sustainability-illustration"><span class="sustainability-illustration-icon">üå±</span><span><strong>Organic & Quality Focus:</strong> Supporting organic farming practices and implementing rigorous quality control from grove to bottle to meet international standards.</span></div>
                </div>
                
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-700 mb-2">Improved Production & Valorization Flow:</h4>
                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
                    <div class="flow-container mb-3">
                        <div class="flow-step"><span class="flow-step-icon">ü´í</span><span class="flow-step-text">Olives (Syrian Cultivars)</span></div>
                        <div class="flow-arrow">‚û°Ô∏è</div>
                        <div class="flow-step"><span class="flow-step-icon">üßº</span><span class="flow-step-text">Washing & Sorting</span></div>
                        <div class="flow-arrow">‚û°Ô∏è</div>
                        <div class="flow-step"><span class="flow-step-icon">‚öôÔ∏è</span><span class="flow-step-text">Crushing</span></div>
                        <div class="flow-arrow">‚û°Ô∏è</div>
                        <div class="flow-step"><span class="flow-step-icon">üîÑ</span><span class="flow-step-text">Malaxation (Controlled Temp.)</span></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flow-container mb-3">
                        <div class="flow-arrow hidden md:flex">‚Ü™Ô∏è</div>
                        <div class="flow-step"><span class="flow-step-icon">üíß</span><span class="flow-step-text">Two-Phase Centrifugal Extraction</span></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                        <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 rounded">
