                            <li>Olive reception, washing, crushing machinery.</li>
                            <li>Malaxers (stainless steel, temperature-controlled).</li>
                            <li>Decanter centrifuge (modern two-phase system preferred).</li>
                            <li>Vertical separators and filters.</li>
                            <li>Stainless steel storage tanks for oil.</li>
                            <li>Bottling, capping, labeling line.</li>
                            <li>Laboratory equipment for quality control.</li>
                            <li>Pomace handling and processing equipment.</li>
                            <li>OMWW treatment system.</li>
                            <li>Utilities (power generation - solar/generator, water connection/borehole).</li>
                            <li>Initial raw material stock & packaging.</li>
                            <li>Licenses, permits, and contingency (15-25%+).</li>
                        </ul>
                         <p class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2"><strong>Note:</strong> Small-scale mills might start from tens of thousands to several hundred thousand USD for core equipment, heavily dependent on capacity, automation, new/used status, and local fabrication capabilities.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-purple-200">
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-purple-700 mb-2">Indicative OPEX (Operational Expenditures) Components (Monthly/Annual):</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-purple-800 space-y-1 cost-list">
                            <li>Raw Olives (seasonal, price highly variable).</li>
                            <li>Labor (skilled and unskilled).</li>
                            <li>Energy (electricity, fuel for machinery/transport).</li>
                            <li>Water (for processing and cleaning).</li>
                            <li>Packaging materials (bottles, caps, labels, cartons).</li>
                            <li>Maintenance, repairs, and spare parts for machinery.</li>
                            <li>Transportation and logistics (inbound olives, outbound products).</li>
                            <li>Quality control testing and certification costs.</li>
                            <li>Waste management (if not fully valorized on-site).</li>
                            <li>Marketing, sales, and distribution expenses.</li>
                            <li>Administrative overheads, rent/lease (if applicable), insurance, taxes.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-700 mt-6 mb-3">Illustrative Bill of Materials (BOM) Components & Indicative International Cost Ranges (Not Syrian Costs)</h4>
                <p class="text-stone-700 mb-2"><strong>CRITICAL DISCLAIMER:</strong> The cost ranges below are highly generalized international estimates for *small-scale/pilot equipment* and DO NOT reflect actual costs in Syria, which are subject to extreme volatility, import duties, supply chain issues, and local conditions. They are for conceptual context ONLY. A detailed, professional feasibility study in Syria is essential.</p>
                <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm">
                    <p class="bom-category">1. Olive Reception & Preparation:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                        <li>Receiving hopper/conveyor, De-leafer/washer: <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $5,000 - $20,000</span></li>
                        <li>Crushing mill (e.g., hammer, disc, for small scale ~500kg/hr): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $8,000 - $25,000</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">2. Olive Paste Processing (Malaxation):</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4"><li>Malaxer units (stainless steel, temp. control, small scale ~200-500kg capacity): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $7,000 - $30,000 per unit</span></li></ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">3. Oil Extraction & Separation:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                        <li>Horizontal centrifugal decanter (two-phase, small scale ~300-700kg/hr paste): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $40,000 - $150,000+ (major cost item)</span></li>
                        <li>Vertical centrifugal separator (polisher, small scale): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $15,000 - $50,000</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">4. Oil Filtration & Storage:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                        <li>Plate/cartridge filters (small capacity): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $2,000 - $10,000</span></li>
                        <li>Stainless steel storage tanks (e.g., 1000-5000L): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $1,000 - $8,000 per tank, depending on size/features</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">5. Bottling & Packaging Line (Semi-Automatic, Small Scale):</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4"><li>Bottle rinser, Filler, Capper, Labeler: <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range for basic semi-auto line: $15,000 - $60,000</span></li></ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">6. Pomace & Wastewater (OMWW) Valorization/Treatment (Basic Small-Scale Setup):</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                        <li>Basic pomace handling (conveyors, simple press): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $5,000 - $20,000</span></li>
                        <li>Small composting setup / Basic OMWW settling tanks & filtration: <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $3,000 - $15,000 (highly variable)</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">7. Utilities & Support Systems (Basic):</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                        <li>Small boiler, Air compressor: <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $5,000 - $20,000</span></li>
                        <li>Basic laboratory equipment (QC): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $2,000 - $10,000</span></li>
                        <li>Solar PV System + Battery Storage (e.g., 20-50kWp solar + commensurate storage): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $20,000 - $70,000+ (highly dependent on scale & battery type)</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">8. General Plant Infrastructure:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4"><li>Piping, valves, pumps, basic control panels: <span class="cost-caveat">Highly variable, could be 10-20% of equipment cost for small plants.</span></li></ul>
                    <p class="font-bold mt-4">Illustrative Total Core Equipment (International Context, Small Scale, Basic): <span class="cost-caveat">Extremely rough international ballpark: $120,000 - $470,000+ (including basic solar). This EXCLUDES land, building, extensive utilities, installation, shipping, duties, licenses, working capital, and contingency, all of which would add substantial costs, especially in Syria.</span></p>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mt-4"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This BOM component list and associated international cost ranges are illustrative and for general context only. A specific feasibility study and engineering design for Syria are essential for any realistic financial planning and detailed BOM creation. Costs are subject to extreme volatility due to inflation, currency fluctuations, supply chain issues, and security context.</p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Sandbox Potential & Strategic Impact</h3>
                <p class="text-stone-700">A model Syrian olive oil facility demonstrating zero-waste, international quality standards, and innovative pomace valorization could transform the sector. It would serve as a benchmark for sustainability and efficiency, attracting further investment and potentially creating a premium "Made in Syria" olive oil brand recognized globally for its quality and eco-credentials.</p>
            </section>
        </div>
        
        <div id="pistachio-milk" class="tab-content hidden">
            <section class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">üå∞ Pistachio Milk: A Deep Dive into a Syrian Opportunity</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">Pistachio milk is an emerging star in the plant-based beverage market. For Syria, a significant pistachio producer, developing value-added products like pistachio milk offers a compelling opportunity to enhance its agricultural sector, cater to global health trends, and establish sustainable, circular economy practices. This section explores the nuances of pistachio milk, from production to market potential and its unique advantages for Syria.</p>
                
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Marketing Edge: Why Syrian Pistachio Milk Stands Out</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="bg-teal-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-teal-200">
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-teal-700 mb-2">The Pistachio Milk Advantage:</h4>
                        <div class="marketing-point"><strong>Unique, Premium Flavor:</strong> Pistachio milk offers a naturally creamy texture and a distinct, subtly sweet, and sophisticated nutty taste that stands out from blander or more common nut milks. It‚Äôs a gourmet experience.</div>
                        <div class="marketing-point"><strong>Nutritional Powerhouse:</strong> Beyond being dairy-free, it's a source of healthy monounsaturated fats, antioxidants (like lutein and zeaxanthin), Vitamin B6, phosphorus, and potassium. It can be lower in calories than some alternatives if unsweetened.</div>
                        <div class="marketing-point"><strong>Allergen-Friendly (Relatively):</strong> While a tree nut, it offers a distinct alternative for consumers allergic to almonds or soy, expanding choices in the plant-based aisle.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-lime-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-lime-200">
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-lime-700 mb-2">The Syrian Origin Advantage:</h4>
                        <div class="marketing-point"><strong>Authenticity & Terroir:</strong> Leverage Syria's heritage as one of the world's top pistachio producers. "Taste the Syrian Sunshine" ‚Äì market the unique flavor profile derived from local cultivars and ancient lands.</div>
                        <div class="marketing-point"><strong>Supporting Syrian Revival:</strong> Each purchase contributes directly to rebuilding livelihoods for Syrian farmers and communities, offering a powerful ethical appeal to conscious consumers.</div>
                        <div class="marketing-point"><strong>Sustainable Choice from a Resilient Land:</strong> Highlight the drought-tolerant nature of pistachio trees, making Syrian pistachio milk a potentially more water-wise choice than almond milk, especially from a region valuing every drop.</div>
                        <div class="marketing-point"><strong>Freshness & Quality:</strong> Promote the potential for "grove-to-glass" processing, ensuring maximum freshness and quality by minimizing transport time for raw nuts.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>


                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">The Allure of Pistachio Milk</h3>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-green-200">
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Nutritional Profile & Health Benefits:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-green-800 space-y-1">
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">ü•õ</span>Naturally lactose-free, dairy-free, soy-free, and often gluten-free.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">ü•ë</span>Good source of healthy fats (monounsaturated and polyunsaturated).</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">‚ú®</span>Contains antioxidants, vitamins (like B6), and minerals (like phosphorus and potassium).</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">‚öñÔ∏è</span>Lower in calories compared to some other nut milks if unsweetened.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">‚ù§Ô∏è</span>May contribute to heart health and blood sugar management.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-200">
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-2">Market Trends & Consumer Appeal:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-amber-800 space-y-1">
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üìà</span>Rapidly growing global plant-based milk market (driven by health, ethics, environment).</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üåü</span>Pistachios perceived as a premium, flavorful nut.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üòã</span>Unique taste profile: subtly sweet, nutty, and distinct.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">üéØ</span>Appeals to consumers seeking novel and gourmet plant-based options.</li>
                            <li><span class="sustainability-point-icon">‚òï</span>Trending ingredient in cafes (lattes, smoothies) and food products.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Sustainable Production & Syrian Advantage</h3>
                 <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">Syria's position as the world's sixth-largest pistachio producer (55,000 MT projected for 2024/25) provides a strong foundation. Leveraging this local resource for pistachio milk can create a higher-value product compared to exporting raw nuts, especially for smaller or unsplit nuts not ideal for whole export.</p>
                
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-700 mb-2">Eco-Friendly Production Aspects:</h4>
                 <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
                    <div class="sustainability-illustration"><span class="sustainability-illustration-icon">üíß</span><span><strong>Water Efficiency:</strong> Pistachio trees are relatively drought-tolerant, making them a more water-sustainable nut source in arid regions like Syria.</span></div>
                    <div class="sustainability-illustration"><span class="sustainability-illustration-icon">üå∞</span><span><strong>Whole Nut Utilization:</strong> Modern processing techniques can utilize the entire pistachio kernel, minimizing food waste.</span></div>
                    <div class="sustainability-illustration"><span class="sustainability-illustration-icon">üöö</span><span><strong>Reduced Carbon Footprint:</strong> Local sourcing and processing of Syrian pistachios drastically reduces transportation emissions.</span></div>
                    <div class="sustainability-illustration"><span class="sustainability-illustration-icon">‚ôªÔ∏è</span><span><strong>By-Product Valorization:</strong> Pistachio shells are converted into valuable biochar (for soil/carbon sequestration) or active compounds, embodying circular economy principles.</span></div>
                </div>


                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-700 mt-4 mb-2">Powering Sustainable Operations: Energy Solutions</h4>
                <p class="text-stone-700 mb-2">The significant energy deficit in Syria presents a major hurdle for any industrial operation. A sustainable pistachio milk factory must address this proactively:</p>
                 <div class="power-illustration">
                    <div class="power-illustration-row">
                        <span class="power-illustration-icon">‚òÄÔ∏è</span>
                        <p class="text-sm">On-Site Solar PV Generation</p>
                        <span class="flow-arrow text-sm mx-1">+</span>
                        <span class="power-illustration-icon">üîã</span>
                        <p class="text-sm">Battery Storage (BESS)</p>
                    </div>
                     <div class="flow-arrow text-sm my-1">‚¨áÔ∏è</div>
                    <div class="power-illustration-row bg-emerald-100 p-2 rounded">
                        <span class="power-illustration-icon">üè≠</span>
                        <p class="text-sm">Factory Operations (Efficient Equipment)</p>
                    </div>
                     <div class="flow-arrow text-sm my-1">‚ôªÔ∏è</div>
                     <div class="power-illustration-row">
                        <span class="power-illustration-icon">üåø</span>
                         <p class="text-sm">Potential Bioenergy from Shell Residues</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-stone-700 mt-2">By implementing these energy solutions (Solar PV + BESS + Efficient Machinery + Potential Bioenergy), the pistachio milk factory can achieve greater operational autonomy, reduce its environmental impact, stabilize energy costs, and truly embody the "eco-friendly" vision.</p>


