                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4"><li>Basic CIP system components (tanks, pump): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $5,000 - $20,000</span></li></ul>
                    <p class="bom-category">7. Shell Valorization (Example: Basic Biochar Kiln):</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4"><li>Small-scale pyrolysis kiln: <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $2,000 - $10,000 (can be locally fabricated for less)</span></li></ul>
                     <p class="bom-category">8. Utilities & Support Systems (Basic):</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                        <li>Small boiler, Chiller: <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $5,000 - $25,000</span></li>
                        <li>Basic laboratory equipment (QC): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $2,000 - $10,000</span></li>
                        <li>Solar PV System + Battery Storage (e.g., 15-40kWp solar + commensurate storage): <span class="cost-caveat">Illustrative International Range: $15,000 - $60,000+</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="font-bold mt-4">Illustrative Total Core Equipment (International Context, Small Scale, Basic): <span class="cost-caveat">Extremely rough international ballpark: $90,000 - $400,000+ (including basic solar). This EXCLUDES land, building, extensive utilities, installation, shipping, duties, licenses, working capital, and contingency, all of which would add substantial costs, especially in Syria.</span></p>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mt-4"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This BOM component list and associated international cost ranges are illustrative and for general context only. A specific feasibility study and engineering design for Syria are essential for any realistic financial planning and detailed BOM creation. Costs are subject to extreme volatility.</p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Challenges & Considerations for Syria</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-stone-700 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Energy Costs:</strong> Processing can be energy-intensive.</li>
                    <li><strong>Quality Consistency:</strong> Ensuring consistent taste, texture, and shelf stability.</li>
                    <li><strong>Market Competition:</strong> Plant-based milk market is competitive.</li>
                    <li><strong>Investment:</strong> Capital for modern processing facility.</li>
                    <li><strong>Water Management:</strong> Sustainable practices in cultivation remain vital.</li>
                </ul>

